**1. What Happened (Context for New Session)**

The 21-day QUANTUM implementation plan was completed. On Day 21 (Feb
17-18), the dashboard was upgraded to v3.2 with Content Preview and
Video Watch modals. Everything was working.

Then in the most recent session (Feb 25-26), a series of changes were
made to the Brief Approval Handler workflow that accidentally broke the
core pipeline. Here is what went wrong:

**1.1 The Mistake**

While attempting to move content review from Telegram to the dashboard,
three critical nodes were removed from the Brief Approval Handler:

  ----------------------- ------------ -----------------------------------
  **Node Removed**        **Should     **Impact**
                          Have Been    
                          Removed?**   

  **Call E2 Webhook**     **NO**       E2 content generation no longer
                                       triggered on Approve

  **Link Content to Brief **NO**       FK link between content_briefs and
  (Update Brief FK)**                  content_logs broken

  **Send Content          **YES (only  Telegram content preview with
  Preview**               this one)**  Publish/Kill buttons
  ----------------------- ------------ -----------------------------------

The ONLY node that should have been removed was Send Content Preview
(since content review was moving to the dashboard). The other two nodes
are core pipeline infrastructure that must remain.

**1.2 The Fix Applied**

Call E2 Webhook and Update Brief FK (Link Content to Brief) nodes were
restored. FK linking was verified working:

> **✅** Brief #120 -\> content_log_id = 80 (FK link confirmed working)

**1.3 Where We Stopped**

The user requested that Send Content Preview be restored so that after
E2 generates content, the full content with scoring appears on Telegram
with Publish/Kill buttons BEFORE anything goes to E3. The session hit
context limit before this could be implemented.

> **⚠️ WARNING:** The user explicitly stated: \'These things should not
> be touched, we were already finished!\' Do NOT modify any core
> pipeline nodes. Only ADD the Send Content Preview node back.

