**3. The Exact Fix Needed**

**ONLY ONE THING NEEDS TO HAPPEN: Add the Send Content Preview node back
into the Brief Approval Handler.**

**3.1 Current Brief Approval Handler Flow (BROKEN)**

> Schedule Trigger -\> Check Telegram -\> Process Approval -\> Update DB
> -\> Telegram Confirm
>
> -\> Check If Approved -\> Call E2 Webhook -\> Update Brief FK -\>
> \[MISSING: Send Content Preview\] -\> ???
>
> -\> Check If Published -\> Call E3 Webhook

**3.2 Required Flow (CORRECT)**

> Schedule Trigger -\> Check Telegram -\> Process Approval -\> Update DB
> -\> Telegram Confirm
>
> -\> Check If Approved -\> Call E2 Webhook -\> Update Brief FK -\> Send
> Content Preview \[STOP HERE\]
>
> (User sees full content on Telegram with Publish/Kill buttons)
>
> (User taps Publish -\> next polling cycle picks it up)
>
> -\> Check If Published -\> Call E3 Webhook

**3.3 Send Content Preview Node Specification**

Type: Code node (JavaScript)

Position: Between Update Brief FK and the end of the approve branch

Data source: Pull from Call E2 Webhook node (NOT from \$json, which is
the PostgreSQL UPDATE output)

Key line: var d = \$(\"Call E2 Webhook\").first().json;

**The node must:**

1\. Only execute for APPROVE actions (skip for publish/reject/kill)

2\. Pull content data from Call E2 Webhook (which has hooks, script,
captions, storyboard, etc.)

3\. Send a formatted Telegram message with all content sections

4\. Include QA status and violations count

5\. Attach Publish/Kill inline keyboard buttons (callback_data:
publish_BRIEFID, kill_BRIEFID)

6\. Handle Telegram 4096 char limit (split if needed)

> **⚠️ WARNING:** Send Content Preview should NOT connect to Call E3
> Webhook. E3 only fires when the user presses Publish on the NEXT
> polling cycle. The flow after Send Content Preview should END (return
> the data and stop). The Publish action is picked up by the Check If
> Published branch separately.

**3.4 Known Working Code (Last Verified Version)**

This code was working before it was accidentally deleted. It should be
restored as-is:

> // First line MUST reference Call E2 Webhook, not \$json
>
> var d = \$(\"Call E2 Webhook\").first().json;
>
> // NOT: var d = \$json; (this gives PostgreSQL UPDATE output, missing
> all content fields)

