**5. Full Pipeline Architecture**

**5.1 Automated Daily Flow**

9:00 AM Cairo: E1 Trend Scout fires via cron

\~9:02 AM: E1 finishes, auto-triggers QUANTUM via webhook

\~9:03 AM: QUANTUM checks existing briefs for deduplication

\~9:04 AM: 3 fresh briefs arrive on Telegram with Approve/Reject buttons

**5.2 Human-in-the-Loop Approval (Two Stages)**

**STAGE 1 - Brief Approval:**

User taps Approve on Telegram -\> Brief Approval Handler catches
callback -\> Updates brief status to \'approved\' -\> Calls E2 Webhook
-\> E2 generates content (Sonnet + 3 QA gates) -\> FK links content to
brief -\> Send Content Preview shows full content on Telegram with
Publish/Kill buttons

**STAGE 2 - Content Publish:**

User reviews content on Telegram -\> Taps Publish or Kill -\> Brief
Approval Handler catches callback -\> If Publish: updates status to
\'published\', calls E3 Webhook -\> E3 routes to correct video tool,
generates placeholder, stores in publish_logs, sends Telegram preview

**5.3 Key Technical Patterns**

n8n Code nodes use: this.helpers.httpRequest() for API calls

Cross-node references: \$(\"NodeName\").first().json for pulling data
from earlier nodes

Webhook settings: \'Using Respond to Webhook Node\' when Webhook
Response nodes exist

PostgreSQL: Two-step pattern (Code node formats SQL -\> PostgreSQL node
executes)

Container networking: Use container names (postgres, qdrant, ollama) not
localhost

**5.4 Telegram Bot Actions**

  --------------- ---------------------- ---------------------------------
  **Action**      **callback_data**      **Effect**

  Approve         approve_BRIEFID        Status-\>approved, E2 fires,
                                         content preview sent

  Reject          reject_BRIEFID         Status-\>rejected, Telegram
                                         confirm

  Publish         publish_BRIEFID        Status-\>published, E3 fires

  Kill            kill_BRIEFID           Status-\>killed, Telegram confirm
  --------------- ---------------------- ---------------------------------

**5.5 Telegram Commands**

/status - System health dashboard with pipeline stats

/stale - Lists pending/approved briefs older than 24 hours

**6. Dashboard Issues (Secondary Priority)**

These are lower priority than the Send Content Preview fix but should be
addressed:

**6.1 Published Tab - \'Not Generated\' Bug**

The Dashboard API v1 workflow SQL query filters content_logs to only
return pending/approved status items. Published items therefore show
\'Not generated\' in the Script preview modal. Fix: Update the SQL query
in Dashboard API v1 to return ALL content_logs regardless of status.

